caption.text:
⭐️ NEW Instagram Feature: “Best Practices”

A few days ago, Instagram added a new section to the “Professional Dashboard” called “Best Practice”

This section is *supposed to* include tips and advice that are specific to your account, in order to create better content and reach more people.

Here’s the problem… ⤵️

after looking at the advice that they gave me + the screenshots of advice that they have been giving other people,

👎 The advice just isn’t great ☹️

I think some of it is helpful & accurate,
but almost none of it seems to be specific.

If you have absolutely no idea what you are doing on Instagram, the “best practices“ might be a hopeful way to get started….

But for most of us, the tips are just vague (for example: “post HD videos!” ….um, duh!

And some of the tips are just WRONG (“videos longer than 30 seconds get the most reach!”) -> According to numerous studies, that’s not accurate.

Have you checked out your “best practices” yet? What do you think??

the COLLAB feature!

Use the comments section on this post to find someone to collab with!

Here are the keys:
1. Find someone with a similar SIZE audience
2. Find someone with a similar audience INTEREST

Example:
- Rock climbing and mountain biking = good collab
- Yoga and functional workouts = great collab
- Video games and dental health = probably a bad collab

DON'T JUST COMMENT, RESPOND TO SOMEONE ELSE! GO!!
